BEYOND TALENTED settled at the back of the field in the beginning stages, was urged left handed inside at the seven sixteenths marker, offered little response and flattened out by the time they entered the top of the stretch.

ABSOLUTE JEWEL broke a little slow to start, could see the field down the backside, shifted out for run five wide in upper stretch and showed good energy the final furlong to be involved at the wire for a share. PICTUREDAY JESSICA rated kindly behind the early speed, saved all the ground inside on the turn, was in with a chance on the rail as they turned for home and offered little finish in the final eighth. MY GIRL HOOTER was unhurried in the early going, travelled four wide stalking outside with three furlongs to go, was fanned out to be six or seven wide at the top of the lane, could not recover and had little in the late stages. RIDERS CLAIM OF FOUL AND STEWARDS INQUIRY #5 HALO STYLE AGAINST #4 CARLAS HONOR AT THE SEVENTY YARD POLE RESULTED IN NO CHANGE
